Two fake doctors have been arrested for selling fraudulent medical certificates. They were taken into custody in a joint operation in Germiston. #eNCA speaks to Christopher Tsatsawane from the HPCSA. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two fake doctors have been arrested for selling fraudulent medical certificates. They were taken into custody in a joint operation in Germiston. The Health Professions Council says it worked with law enforcement agencies after a community tip-off. READ: Increased number of bogus doctors worries HPCSA "The kind of medical certificates are basically bogus and these are certificates that were making use of doctors who actually did not exist in terms of our register," said Christopher Tsatsawane. "So in a nutshell, these are bogus practitioners who were actually taking advantage of our unsuspecting members of the public.”